Merge pull request #258 from mochr/Fix_Swift_4_1_bugs

Fix Swift 4.1 bugs
Removed two string-tests, as the functions they were using are deprecated, and also a part of the Swift language. No PerfectSoft code were tested in these tests.
Changed the deallocate(capacity:_) to deallocate(), as the use of deallocate(capacity:_) is deprecated in Swift 4.1.
Added an explicit String constructor to create a string from a substring. This was suggested by the Swift 4.1 migration guide.

Add ability to 'even out' logs

If you read log files in plaintext, like I do, having the lines be different lengths is annoying. This adds an opt-in way to make the log messages flush with each other:

even = false (default)
```
[INFO] Starting server in mode 'debug'
[INFO] mustacheRoot: /Users/[redacted]/Desktop/Programming/Swift/Perfect/[redacted]/Web/templates/public
[INFO] Starting [redacted] core...
[INFO] Initializing StORM
[ERR] The operation couldn’t be completed. (MongoDB.BSONError error 0.)
[INFO] Starting server...
```

even = true
```
[INFO] Starting server in mode 'debug'
[INFO] mustacheRoot: /Users/[redacted]/Desktop/Programming/Swift/Perfect/[redacted]/Web/templates/public
[INFO] Starting [redacted] core...
[INFO] Initializing StORM
[ERR]  The operation couldn’t be completed. (MongoDB.BSONError error 0.)
[INFO] Starting server...
```

Note: this ties in with PerfectlySoft/Perfect-Logger#1
